UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You\'ve already done me a great service, $N. For that I thank you.$B$BThe least I can do now is tell you what brought me here: My long time friend Trey Lightforge and I came to Jaedenar to investigate the Shadow Council when they caught us unprepared. They took Trey deeper into Shadow Hold and put me in here after taking all of our equipment... I can still hear his screams from below, $N. They were... inhuman. I don\'t know what they\'ve done to him, but they will pay for it.',Text0_1_loc9='You\'ve already done me a great service, $N. For that I thank you.$B$BThe least I can do now is tell you what brought me here: My long time friend Trey Lightforge and I came to Jaedenar to investigate the Shadow Council when they caught us unprepared. They took Trey deeper into Shadow Hold and put me in here after taking all of our equipment... I can still hear his screams from below, $N. They were... inhuman. I don\'t know what they\'ve done to him, but they will pay for it.',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4113;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='As you inspect the cage and the Night elf inside, you get an odd sense of deja vu. For some reason she does not make eye contact with you--it is almost as if you are not there to her.',Text0_1_loc9='As you inspect the cage and the Night elf inside, you get an odd sense of deja vu. For some reason she does not make eye contact with you--it is almost as if you are not there to her.',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4114;
Text0_0_loc9='They don\'t realize that they\'re dead, $R. They are cursed to relive the last memory they had before the town was eaten alive from the inside out. Most of them, anyway. Some were less fortunate.$B$BYou thought the Scourge did this? The Scourge did not yet exist and if they had, we would have at least put up a damned fight.$B$BNo, this was the result of a plague that came out of Scholomance and ravaged the town. It was horrifying and devastating. None survived.$B$BNow leave me to my sorrows.'
Text0_0_loc9='Can\'t you see we\'re trying to prepare for Uther\'s visit? Now get out of my way, I have much work to do!',Text0_1_loc9='Can\'t you see we\'re trying to prepare for Uther\'s visit? Now get out of my way, I have much work to do!',Text1_0_loc9='Have you tried our bread? Baker Masterson must be the most gifted chef to have ever lived!'
Text2_0_loc9='Welcome to Caer Darrow, stranger.',Text3_0_loc9='We\'re not really rude people, stranger, it\'s just that everyone is in a rush, trying to make sure that everything is perfect for Uther\'s arrival. It\'s not often that the Lightbringer comes to town.'
Text4_0_loc9='Another lovely day on our beautiful island.'
Text0_0_loc9='Watch your step, stranger. We do not allow miscreants in our town.',Text0_1_loc9='Watch your step, stranger. We do not allow miscreants in our town.',Text1_0_loc9='I\'ve got my eye on you, $R.'
Text2_0_loc9='I have a lot of pent up anger and hostility. Just give me a reason, guttersnipe.',Text3_0_loc9='Why, you look like a common street urchin!'
Text4_0_loc9='There\'s no loitering, pan handling, cursing, fighting, or anything else you\'re thinking about doing, allowed in Caer Darrow.'
Text0_0_loc9='The Cult of the Damned has grown large in scope. Nearly every city, from the capitals to the small hamlets and hovels of both the Horde and Alliance, have Cult members hidden amongst their citizenry.$B$BDo not look so surprised. The Cult only wears a uniform for ritual and ceremony. It is quite possible that you have interacted with one during your adventures and not even known.'
Text0_0_loc9='Is it? This has always been their method of operation. What is of greater value to Kel\'Thuzad and the ever growing Scourge army? A zealous, living, follower that can work their way into a society and then unleash a plague, destroying thousands; or a single undead trooper? Certainly you cannot be that dense$B$BYes, $R, they live, work, and plot among you.'
Text0_0_loc9='Stop - no. Slow down - maybe.$B$BThe Scholomance is their primary source of training and education. It is from there that the Cult members fan out and ultimately, make their way into our societies.$B$BThat is why we must strike at the source. The very heart of the Cult of the Damned!'
Text0_0_loc9='Slow down, $R. The one you need to kill is already dead. Killing him again will serve no purpose. There are very few ways in which a lich can actually be destroyed and none of those means are available to you or I. That is why I have a plan. A plan that will have a very noticeable and real impact upon the Cult.'
Text0_0_loc9='It\'s simple, really. Rob the lich, Ras Frostwhisper, of his powers. Return him to his mortal form and then slay him, once and for all.'
Text0_0_loc9='Ah, I suppose that I am getting ahead of myself. Ras Frostwhisper is the overseer of this school. The being responsible for training all of its Dark Masters. A lieutenant and favored pupil of Kel\'Thuzad. He was once a hedge mage of Stromgarde: A rogue wizard that never received his formal training from Dalaran.$B$BWhen Kel\'Thuzad opened the Cult, Ras was among the first to join his ranks. Ras knew that through dark magic, he would find immortality.'
Text0_0_loc9='And find it he did. After quickly advancing through the ranks of the Cult, the Lich King himself granted Ras immortality. Thus was born Ras Frostwhisper, the lich.$B$BNow do you understand?'
Text0_0_loc9='Good. In order to carry out my plan, we must first create a lifestone. Are you prepared to act?'
Text0_0_loc9='Some were spared the anguish that memories provide.'
Text0_0_loc9='The Barov house sure does keep me busy. Always some sort of refuse coming out of there.',Text1_0_loc9='My job title is Waste Management Specialist.'
Text2_0_loc9='Perhaps you should speak into these sound enhancing devices attached to my FISTS OF FURY.',Text3_0_loc9='Ah, my sweet Brandy, I miss her so!'
Text0_0_loc9='Well met, friend.  I am Officer Garush, and I am a proud member of a world-wide organization known as the Argent Dawn.  Our cause is to fight swiftly and mercilessly against any element of evil that surfaces in Azeroth.  We are not a political body, nor do we ever wish to become one.  Our cause is singular, and to that end we call both the Horde and Alliance as friends - friends in the cause of stamping out evil!$B$BFor the Dawn, my $G brother : sister;!'
