UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='While Cyndra is not bubbly like her potions, her kind manner is suitable for teaching her trade.  You can find her just east of the Inn in Dolanaar.',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='Cyndra\'s knowledge in alchemy is somewhat limited, but I\'m sure it would be sufficient to get you started.  She practices her craft just east of the Inn in Dolanaar.',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4329;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Zarrin seems to have a good knowledge of the cooking trade.  Why don\'t you go see if he will show you some recipes?  He is usually cooking over by the Inn in Dolanaar.',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='We could certainly use another cook around Dolanaar, not that Zarrin\'s cooking is lacking mind you.  Why don\'t you go see what he can teach you?',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4330;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Alanna Raveneye attributes part of her talent in enchanting to her communion with the spirits at the Oracle Glade.  You should be able to find her there now.',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='Alanna spends most of her day at the Oracle Glade where she practices her profession.  Should you wish to learn the Enchanter\'s profession you will need to go there to find her.',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4331;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Byancie has often lent her services to the sentinels who patrol the local wilds.  You should talk to her if you desire to learn First Aid.',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='Byancie\'s skill in First Aid has proven useful on numerous occasions.  You can find her just north of the Inn in Dolanaar if you wish to learn from her.',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4332;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='All the fisherman have moved to Darnassus with the recent attacks around Lake Al\'Ameth.  You should try looking for someone to train you there.',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='The Timberlings have made it too difficult for the fishermen to catch anything around Dolanaar.  You best look for someone to train you in Darnassus.',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4333;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Malorne somehow manages to pick the most delicate herbs without damaging them.  Certainly he is the one you should learn from.  He lives just east of the Inn in Dolanaar.',Text0_1_loc9='Malorne somehow manages to pick the most delicate herbs without damaging them.  Certainly he is the one you should learn from.  He lives just east of the Inn in Dolanaar.',Text1_0_loc9='Herbalism requires a gentle touch that few such as Malorne can teach.  Seek him out east of the Inn in Dolanaar.',Text1_1_loc9='Herbalism requires a gentle touch that few such as Malorne can teach.  Seek him out east of the Inn in Dolanaar.' WHERE entry=4334;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The Maneweavers practice their professions out of their home on the road to Darnassus.  Nadyia is an excellent teacher when it comes to Leatherworking.  You should see what she can teach you.',Text0_1_loc9='The Maneweavers practice their professions out of their home on the road to Darnassus.  Nadyia is an excellent teacher when it comes to Leatherworking.  You should see what she can teach you.',Text1_0_loc9='Nadyia has made quite the leatherworker in her years of practice.  Travel west on the road to Darnassus to pay her a visit and maybe she can bestow some of her knowledge upon you.',Text1_1_loc9='Nadyia has made quite the leatherworker in her years of practice.  Travel west on the road to Darnassus to pay her a visit and maybe she can bestow some of her knowledge upon you.' WHERE entry=4335;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You can find Radnaal practicing his craft outside his home on the road to Darnassus.  You should stop by and see what he can teach you.',Text0_1_loc9='You can find Radnaal practicing his craft outside his home on the road to Darnassus.  You should stop by and see what he can teach you.',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4336;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I am certain there is a Tailor that could provide you training in Darnassus.  When you arrive, ask one of the Sentinels in Darnassus about seeing a Tailor.',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='Many of the supplies the tailors need come by way of Darnassus.  It is not surprising that they all moved there to work.  If you wish to be a tailor then you best head to Darnassus.',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4337;
Text0_0_loc9='Hello, $C. I\'ve set up camp here at the Bulwark to make my preparations for my journey into the Plaguelands. I\'ve heard rumor that a great human wizard took up residency in Hearthglen not terribly long ago. He was commissioned by the Scarlet Crusade to fashion their warriors and hunters new bows and guns. It\'s said that he completed a remarkable weapon before the Crusade killed him.$B$BI guess their mistrust of the arcane has grown.'
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Greetings, $C. Don\'t have too much time to talk--I\'m just using Chillwind as a camp to get some rest before heading to Hearthglen. I\'ve heard word that before they went crazy, the Scarlet Crusade had a mage working for them who was trying to create powerful bows and guns for their soldiers. I\'m not sure if he succeeded or not... the Crusade killed him before any of his finished product made it out. Maybe they killed him to keep it a secret... or maybe they distrust the arcane that much.',Text0_1_loc9='Greetings, $C. Don\'t have too much time to talk--I\'m just using Chillwind as a camp to get some rest before heading to Hearthglen. I\'ve heard word that before they went crazy, the Scarlet Crusade had a mage working for them who was trying to create powerful bows and guns for their soldiers. I\'m not sure if he succeeded or not... the Crusade killed him before any of his finished product made it out. Maybe they killed him to keep it a secret... or maybe they distrust the arcane that much.',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4354;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='He... hello, $N. Sorry, I\'m recovering from my wounds.$B$BThose Scarlet Crusaders are tougher than I had given them credit for. They almost did me in.$B$BYou should be careful too. I\'d hate to see them get the jump on you.',Text0_1_loc9='He... hello, $N. Sorry, I\'m recovering from my wounds.$B$BThose Scarlet Crusaders are tougher than I had given them credit for. They almost did me in.$B$BYou should be careful too. I\'d hate to see them get the jump on you.',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4355;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='My family worked  the Northridge Lumber Mill in what\'s now Western Plaguelands. They were dedicated to the Dumah family, and now the Scarlet Crusade have taken it over along with all of Hearthglen!$B$BI will not rest until those zealots are wiped from Azeroth.',Text0_1_loc9='My family worked  the Northridge Lumber Mill in what\'s now Western Plaguelands. They were dedicated to the Dumah family, and now the Scarlet Crusade have taken it over along with all of Hearthglen!$B$BI will not rest until those zealots are wiped from Azeroth.',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=4356;
Text0_0_loc9='Long ago, before the last great war, my father ran the Northridge Lumber Mill. It was his life, and he was committed to it. Then the war came, and as much as it pained him, we had to flee to Stormwind.$B$BWe lost a number of friends and family in those days, and it pains me to know that the Scarlet Crusade has taken the mill for their own ends.$B$BThat\'s why I\'ve returned.'
Text0_0_loc9='We are the last of the furbolg race... The Timbermaw tribe remains uncorrupted, yet we face the same hostility from outsiders; most believe that it is not possible... that there could actually be furbolg that escaped the corruption...$B$BAngry at those that strive to make enemies too quickly, my brethren now attack any that draw near; they trust no one.$B$BBut perhaps, if you strive to make your presence peaceful with them, they might look upon you as an ally.'
Text0_0_loc9='You must find a way to show that you both are fighting for the same side. Although the Timbermaw may attack you now, if you are diligent, you will find a way.$B$BYou must remember that any attacks on the Timbermaw furbolg directly will greatly hinder your chances of gaining them as an ally.$B$BA good place to start would be the Deadwood furbolg found in many parts of Felwood. These furbolg are the enemy of the Timbermaw tribe, and slaying them would greatly improve your standing with the Timbermaw.'
Text0_0_loc9='We Timbermaw can grant you safe passage through the hold, however, you must prove yourself worthy of our aid.'
Text0_0_loc9='The Winterfall furbolg that reside here in Winterspring were once our allies... But one day, that all changed.$B$BDriven by the strange demands of their high chief, they began to attack all others that they came in contact with, including our tribe. They keep to themselves now...'
Text0_0_loc9='I trust very few of your kind, $N. But I can tell that you are a friend.'
Text0_0_loc9='Yes, yes. I see you.$B$BBe on your way. You may have earned the trust of a few, but it will take more than that to prove it to me!'
Text0_0_loc9='If you prove that you are a true ally, I might consider training you...'
