Text0_0_loc9='Maybe you do better at getting back prized Gordok relic from creepy Highborne prince than da old boss did!'
Text0_0_loc9='Hail to da new king!',Text1_0_loc9='When I scowled at you before you became da new king... um... I was just joking.$B$BYeah!'
Text2_0_loc9='Dem other ogres was dumb to attack you, boss!  Dat\'s why I\'m still alive - I\'m smart and stuff!',Text3_0_loc9='We a lot cleaner than da ogres in Tanaris.  All over da desert as far as da eye can see - ogre poo.  Not here, no $G sir : ma\'am;!'
Text4_0_loc9='So long as you stay here with us, you da king.  You take off, and some other ogre will take your place.  That\'s da way of da Gordok!',Text5_0_loc9='I am so smart!  S-M-R-T!'
Text6_0_loc9='Old king got dead?  That\'s unpossible!',Text7_0_loc9='I cause you no trouble, boss.'
Text0_0_loc9='If you not talk to Mizzle, you not become da king!  Take to Mizzle da Crafty!',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:'
Text0_0_loc9='So... you took out the King eh?  I knew that these bozos would make you the new king, I just knew it!  That\'s all these bozos understand - power.$B$BIt would seem that the more henchmen you keep alive, the higher your tribute will be.  Not to shabby - makes for an interesting challenge I\'d say.  If you leave, I wouldn\'t expect to remain king.  One of these yokels will no doubt step up and take your place.$B$BOne more thing... you didn\'t happen to find my key, did you?'
Text0_0_loc9='What you must understand is that being able to index 10,000 years of existence has given me a rather unique perspective on life. Your present day trials and tribulations are meaningless.'
Text0_0_loc9='Oh the drama and fuss the young Master exerted. You would think the fate of the world rested squarely on his shoulders. Only mortals could have such a skewed perspective on our world.$B$BAlas, he left me with his meager magical secrets... Librams or some such nonsense. I have no use for these paultry magics but perhaps you might be interested in their enchantments.'
Text0_0_loc9='They\'ve been stolen, $R! Three of our most prized volumes. Should you return the tomes, a reward will most certainly be yours.'
