Text0_0_loc9='Be careful going into the thicket, $C.  There is a harmful aura lingering about the place.  It must be the residue from whatever destroyed my fellow druids.'
Text0_0_loc9='This forest be a spooky place.  It\'s full of more bad juju than just the Alliance, so you watch out for yourself.'
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The Horde isn\'t the only danger in this forest. Don\'t let its seeming tranquility fool you.',Text0_1_loc9='The Horde isn\'t the only danger in this forest. Don\'t let its seeming tranquility fool you.',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=9393;
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You\'re definitely strong, $R, but do you have what it takes to become the Warmaul champion?',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=9394;
Text0_0_loc9='Get out of my way, $R. Can\'t you see that we\'re in the middle of a battle!'
Text0_0_loc9='Outstanding! Killing a Pit Lord such as Azgalor is no small feat, my friend. If we had more time, I would love to hear the story of you and your companions. Archimonde will not give us that pause, however. My scouts have already reported that the Legion is amassing an immense force outside our camp, and Archimonde is very close to the World Tree. We are evacuating with the help of Lady Proudmoore. You should head to the World Tree at once. The fate of our world is still undecided.'
Text0_0_loc9='The corpse of one of the Broken lies here.  Mysteriously, the cause of its death does not appear to be from one of the mutated moths.$B$BPerhaps it has something to do with the strange object resting right next to its outstretched hand?'
Text0_0_loc9='Hail, champion! Have you ever thought about going into the gladiator business full time? You and I could make a mountain of gold.'
Text0_0_loc9='Very busy... very busy!  What?'
Text0_0_loc9='Now that I\'ve been beaten to within an inch of my life what do you want?'
Text0_0_loc9='We\'ll get to the bottom of this massacre if it\'s the last thing we do!'
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The moment we\'ve been dreading is now at hand, $C. Archimonde has made his way to Nordrassil, and is beginning to devour the World Tree\'s energies. Malfurion needs more time for his plan to work, so we must do the unthinkable. You must attack Archimonde directly, while my own troops hold off the streams of Burning Legion forces approaching the top of the mount.',Text0_1_loc9='The moment we\'ve been dreading is now at hand, $C. Archimonde has made his way to Nordrassil, and is beginning to devour the World Tree\'s energies. Malfurion needs more time for his plan to work, so we must do the unthinkable. You must attack Archimonde directly, while my own troops hold off the streams of Burning Legion forces approaching the top of the mount.',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=9410;
Text0_0_loc9='Welcome to the Taverns of Time!',Text1_0_loc9='Rest your weary feet, we have all the time in the world...'
Text2_0_loc9='Can I offer you a drink? I promise you its aged like none other!'
Text0_0_loc9='What do you see when you look to the west, mortal?'
Text0_0_loc9='Do you know what I see? A precursor to invasion.$B$BAye, the master was wise in sealing the portals but has since lost his... how shall I put this? The master has lost his focus. Yes... Focus.$B$BWith this loss, the Legion has seized opportunity. They seep out now, growing in number day by day.',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:'
Text0_0_loc9='The Burning Legion. Demons. I see them as clearly as you can see your own hand in front of your face. That is, I used to be able to see them clearly.$B$BWith the Legion\'s return come new machinations. Under normal circumstances, I am able to sense the presence of a demon from a thousand paces.$B$B<Altruis grimaces.>',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:'
Text0_0_loc9='They elude me. I cannot see past their defenses. They have put in place wards to prevent detection.$B$B<Altruis points westward.>$B$BThey fear us because they know that we fear nothing. The cost for such power is great, the sacrifices many.',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:'
Text0_0_loc9='<Altruis turns to face you and smiles.>$B$BI do not.$B$B<Altruis points to his steed, Nethrandamus.>$B$BWe must stop them before these forge camps are able to complete whatever it is that they are building.',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:'
Text0_0_loc9='That is what these structures that litter the landscape are called. The Legion have employed the mo\'arg and gan\'arg to build weapons of mass destruction at these mobile forge camps. Let us not find out what it is that they intend to build here in Nagrand!$B$BYou will be my eyes. Your weapons will be my fury.',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:'
Text0_0_loc9='Oh no, not you again!  Go away!'
Text0_0_loc9='This is what I have gathered from the information that you collected from the survey.$B$BThere are two primary forge camps: Forge Camp: Hate, directly west of where we stand and Forge Camp: Fear, directly southwest. Each camp has a Legion transporter, one forge, and several spell warding towers. Additionally, the camps are guarded by wrathguards manning fel cannons. Lastly, each camp has a pit lord overseer.$B$BRight then, this should be no problem at all...$B$B<Altruis laughs.>',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:'
