Text0_0_loc9='Be wary, for the plagued tendrils of the Lich King lurk close.',Text0_1_loc9='Be wary, for the plagued tendrils of the Lich King lurk close.'
Text0_0_loc9='The outhouse appears to be occupied at the moment.'
Text0_0_loc9='May the Light purge your infection, brave $N.',Text0_1_loc9='May the Light purge your infection, brave $N.'
Text0_0_loc9='My father has gifted me with his battle armor and axe. Soon I put it to good use.'
Text0_0_loc9='Fortunately, the outhouse is currently vacant.'
Text0_0_loc9='Our food and drink are in short supply.  I\'m afraid I do not have anything to offer you.',Text0_1_loc9='Our food and drink are in short supply.  I\'m afraid I do not have anything to offer you.'
Text0_0_loc9='Thank you for your help, $N.  These frostberries are literally the fruits of your labor.',Text0_1_loc9='Thank you for your help, $N.  These frostberries are literally the fruits of your labor.'
Text0_0_loc9='I once roamed the Grizzly Hills, son to the great Ursoc, who ruled over this land.$B$BBut now... now I\'m doomed to spend the rest of my life in this cave.'
Text0_0_loc9='You don\'t understand.  If I wanted to I could fight my way out of this cave.$B$BIt\'s my father, Ursoc.  He has returned from the dead... but he\'s not the same.$B$BHe gave his life during the War of the Ancients thousands of years ago.  For centuries, the furbolg who worshipped him tried to devise a way to resurrect him.$B$BFinally they decided they were to attempt to regrow the failed world tree, Vordrassil, and use its magic to bring back my father.'
Text0_0_loc9='Keep your voice down, $C. I\'m in disguise and spying for Venomspite.',Text0_1_loc9='Keep your voice down, $C. I\'m in disguise and spying for Venomspite.'
Text0_0_loc9='The sapling they grew bore a fruit.  At first it seemed to work.  Ursoc did come back and I was filled with joy for a brief moment.$B$BAs he recovered, it was clear that he wasn\'t the same.  Neither were the furbolg.$B$BWhatever evil caused the ancient druids to tear down Vordrassil manifested itself in the new tree and turned them all into monsters filled with bloodlust.$B$BThe thing that now walks the Grizzly Hills is not my father and it must be put to rest.'
Text0_0_loc9='I am Kodian, daughter of Ursoc.  I watch over this once sacred shrine.$B$BI\'ve not seen a stranger come here in a long time.'
Text0_0_loc9='A furbolg named Tur Ragepaw.  Not one of ours.$B$BThis one came from the southern lands.  He was of the Timbermaw tribe.$B$BHe wanted to see Ursoc.  He seemed to think that Vordrassil\'s taint could be purified and used to save my father.$B$BIt is foolish to entertain such hopes.  You will agree when you see the darkness that has afflicted him like I have.'
Text0_0_loc9='Think you could get me out of here, $C?',Text0_1_loc9='Think you could get me out of here, $C?'
Text0_0_loc9='Oh good, you\'re here to rescue me. Now let me out of here!'
Text0_0_loc9='Hey, $G buddy : ma\'am;. I\'ve seen you around.$B$BMind getting me out of here?'
Text0_0_loc9='I don\'t know what happened. I had just arrived at Venomspite and then all of a sudden I woke up in this cage!$B$BAre you here to rescue me?'
